<main class="site-main static-page about-page">
    <header class="static-header text-left" style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-accent); padding-bottom: var(--space-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl); display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;">
        <h1 class="text-4xl" style="margin-bottom: 0; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--color-text-base); line-height: 1;">I am RedCamel.</h1>
        <h2 class="text-muted" style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 400; max-width: 480px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">And I built erase.to because I was tired of digital footprints.</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="static-content" style="padding-top: 0; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
        
        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);">
            <h2 style="font-size: 0.9rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);">The Project</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;"><strong>erase.to</strong> is a Zero-Trace communication tool designed by RedCamel. It is built to be an uncompromising, zero-knowledge handoff environment where sensitive data exists only in volatile RAM.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: var(--space-md);">Privacy is not a premium feature. This service is free, runs without ads, and uses no third-party CDNs. I have systematically removed all IP logging and tracking. Even rate limiting is handled through anonymous, stateless Proof-of-Work (PoW), making the infrastructure blind to your identity by design.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8; margin-top: var(--space-md);">Your data is encrypted locally in the browser. Decryption happens purely in your device's RAM, with strict 'No-Store' policies preventing browser caching. Once a message is consumed or expires, it is physically wiped. No logs, no backups, no traces.</p>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);">
            <h2 style="font-size: 0.9rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);">Source Code</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">The core of erase.to is open and auditable. You should not have to take privacy claims on faith. The repository covers everything that matters: how encryption works in the browser, how the fragment key is handled, what the server stores, how single-use and expiry work, and which security headers are set.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">
                <a href="https://github.com/RedCamel1312/erase.to" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem;">
                    <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M12 0C5.374 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23A11.509 11.509 0 0 1 12 5.803c1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576C20.566 21.797 24 17.3 24 12c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
                    github.com/RedCamel1312/erase.to
                </a>
            </p>
        </section>

